definition: to enter a pass/to go through customs
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]
mountain pass/to close/to shut/to turn off/to concern/to involve
surname Guan

sentences.english: In late November, Northeast Field Army was ordered into the customs.
sentences.chinese: 月下旬，东北野战军奉命入关。

sentences.english: After entering Shanhai Pass the transition of Manchu material culture expressed different trend in different areas.
sentences.chinese: 入关后满族物质文化变迁具有明显的地域性差异。

sentences.english: Chlorpheniramine was regarded as a drug in Australia, so you must remember not to carry it to Australia.
sentences.chinese: 扑尔敏被澳大利亚视为毒品，故千万不要带入关。

sentences.english: Yes, all the baggage should be cleared at the first entry port into the United States.
sentences.chinese: 是的，所有进入美国的行李都在最先入关验关。

sentences.english: We definitely can't let these smuggled cars go through customs.
sentences.chinese: 我们绝对不能让这批走私汽车入关。

sentences.english: Polices say a suspect burst into Gwantney's office and fired three shots.
sentences.chinese: 警方称一名嫌犯冲入关特尼的办公室，开了三枪。

sentences.english: Since the entry after the Manchus, China's national ideology, are gradually eliminated.
sentences.chinese: 自满族入关以后，中国的民族思想，便渐渐消灭了。

sentences.english: Before entering Sanhai Pass the material culture of Manchu was in a fast development and transition phrase.
sentences.chinese: 入关前满族物质文化处于一个快速发展与变迁的阶段。
